y follow the same routine my kids do or they don't get game time they do their work some of their projects i assist them their ages are from of them as well a habit takes days to make and days to break the least try it and also get to the library take him out of his usuall enviornment let him pick out some books the magic tree house harry potter series and double fudge are popular in my home of four boys oldest is only though hope i helped and keep us posted keep talking with kids you actually have to repeat the same things for about years see you have about years of repeating to go i have a one year old so i have more than you see good luck Extreme Programming Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix Rule of St Benedict Animal Crossing The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an The Catcher in the Rye Breakfast Poker jargon Hogwarts Narcolepsy Theory of conduct Milton H. Erickson Harrow School GED Mnemonic Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 AFI 100 Years series Urinary incontinence Social rule Jeopardy! Game show Episodes of Lost (Season 1) The Sims The Life and Times of Juniper Lee Shaggy dog story Diazepam The Amazing Race Hansel und Gretel English grammar Sleep Yoga Sutras of Patanjali History of Test cricket (1884 to 1889) The Giver Fecal incontinence Ned's Declassified School Survival Guide The Contender (television series) Hermione Granger New York Giants A Course In Miracles Ron Weasley The Price Is Right Norway national football team Social psychology International League Jon Secada Insomnia Surveillance Dog training Ravi Shastri Apollo 8 USS Yorktown (CV-10) Socrates Aerial (dance move) 1957 World Series Big Brother (Australian TV series) Breath of Fire III Boarding school Speed reading Practices of Jehovah's Witnesses Monster Rancher monsters $ale of the Century Doraemon Little Britain About a Boy Dance Dance Revolution EXTREME 